## Technology Stack & Why Each Choice

### Backend: Express.js + Node.js
| Aspect | Choice | Why |
|--------|--------|-----|
| **Runtime** | Node.js 20 LTS | Same language as frontends (JS everywhere), huge ecosystem |
| **Framework** | Express.js | Industry standard, minimal boilerplate, massive community, easy to learn |
| **Why not Next.js API routes?** | We have TWO separate frontends (citizen + dashboard) вҖ” Next.js works best as a unified full-stack app |
| **Why not Spring Boot?** | Adds Java complexity; the entire project is JS-based, keeping one language reduces cognitive overhead |
| **Why not NestJS?** | Great framework but heavier вҖ” Express is more transparent for learning how backend architecture works |

### Database: PostgreSQL via Supabase
| Aspect | Choice | Why |
|--------|--------|-----|
| **Database** | PostgreSQL | Gold standard relational DB, ACID-compliant, JSON support, full-text search |
| **Hosting** | Supabase (already configured) | Free tier, managed PostgreSQL, built-in auth, storage, real-time, RLS |
| **ORM** | Supabase JS Client (server-side) | Direct integration, auto-generates types, handles connections |
| **Why not raw SQL?** | Supabase client gives us RLS enforcement + connection pooling for free |

### Frontends: React + Vite
| Aspect | Choice | Why |
|--------|--------|-----|
| **Build Tool** | Vite | 10x faster than CRA (which is deprecated), HMR, ESM-native |
| **UI Library** | React 19 | Already used in dashboard, latest features (transitions, suspense) |
| **Icons** | Lucide React (dashboard) + custom SVGs (app) | Consistent, tree-shakeable |
| **CSS** | Vanilla CSS with CSS custom properties | Full control, no build dependency, theming via variables |

### Security Stack
| Layer | Tool | What it prevents |
|-------|------|-----------------|
| **HTTP Headers** | `helmet` | XSS, clickjacking, MIME sniffing, content injection |
| **CORS** | `cors` | Unauthorized cross-origin requests |
| **Rate Limiting** | `express-rate-limit` | DoS attacks, API abuse, brute force login |
| **Input Sanitization** | `express-validator` + `xss` | SQL injection, XSS payloads, malformed data |
| **Auth** | Supabase Auth (JWT) | Unauthorized access, session hijacking |
| **DB Security** | Row Level Security (RLS) | Data leaks, privilege escalation |
| **API Key Protection** | Server-side Gemini calls | API key theft from browser devtools |

### AI: Google Gemini
| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Model** | `gemini-2.0-flash` (fast, cost-effective) |
| **Use Case 1** | Image analysis вҶ’ generate title + description |
| **Use Case 2** | Smart department categorization (Water Dept, Roads, Electricity, etc.) |
| **Use Case 3** | Draft official complaints |
| **Security** | API key stored in server `.env`, never exposed to client |

